│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp"]], "thoughts": "1. Understanding the │
│ Issue:\nThe crash occurs due to an assertion failure in isSingleSourceMaskImpl         │
│ triggered by isExtractSubvectorMask. The assertion states that a shuffle mask element  │
│ is out-of-bounds. This indicates that the SLP vectorizer is calling                    │
│ isExtractSubvectorMask with a mask that contains indices not valid for the expected    │
│ operand element count, violating the preconditions of the IR utility function.\n\n2.   │
│ Analyzing opt's Log:\nFrom the provided debug log, the SLP pass builds and attempts to │
│ vectorize a large bundle of compares (VF=32). During shuffle creation,                 │
│ BaseShuffleAnalysis::isIdentityMask is called with a mask of length 32 and a target    │
│ vector type with VF=4 in a context where it tries to treat the mask as an              │
│ extract-subvector starting at index 0. Specifically, the call stack shows:\n-          │
│ BaseShuffleAnalysis::isIdentityMask(ArrayRef<int> Mask, FixedVectorType *VecTy, bool   │
│ IsStrict)\n- Inside isIdentityMask, it calls                                           │
│ ShuffleVectorInst::isExtractSubvectorMask(Mask, VF, Index) without validating that the │
│ mask size or elements are suitable for that API.\nThe debugger shows                   │
│ isExtractSubvectorMask invoked with Mask of length 32 and NumSrcElts=4.                │
│ isExtractSubvectorMask expects a mask where elements are in the range [0,              │
│ 2*NumSrcElts), meaning [0, 8) here. A 32-length mask built for a larger vector likely  │
│ contains elements >=8, triggering the assertion.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nIn        │
│ BaseShuffleAnalysis::isIdentityMask, the code attempts to detect identity masks in     │
│ non-strict mode by using ShuffleVectorInst::isExtractSubvectorMask(Mask, VF, Index)    │
│ (lines ~7991-7994). However, it does not guard this call with a condition that ensures │
│ the mask size and values are compatible with                                           │
│ isExtractSubvectorMask.\nisExtractSubvectorMask is designed to analyze a mask of size  │
│ equal to the result vector length (or 2*NumSrcElts in certain contexts) and elements   │
│ bounded by NumOpElts*2. Passing a mask of larger length (e.g., 32) or with indices     │
│ exceeding the allowed range causes an assertion.\nTherefore, the SLP code misuses the  │
│ IR utility by calling isExtractSubvectorMask on masks that are not of appropriate      │
│ size/value range. This is the earliest transformation point leading to the             │
│ failure.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nEdit the call site in                          │
│ BaseShuffleAnalysis::isIdentityMask to only call isExtractSubvectorMask when the mask  │
│ length equals the vector length (VF). This ensures the mask elements are expected to   │
│ be within the bounds required by the function.\n\nEdit at                              │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp lines 7991-7994:\nReplace:\n  if       │
│ (!IsStrict) {\n    // Consider extract subvector starting from index 0.\n    if        │
│ (ShuffleVectorInst::isExtractSubvectorMask(Mask, VF, Index) &&\n        Index == 0)\n  │
│ return true;\n    ...\n  }\nWith:\n  if (!IsStrict) {\n    // Consider extract         │
│ subvector starting from index 0, only if mask size matches VF.\n    if (Limit == VF    │
│ &&\n        ShuffleVectorInst::isExtractSubvectorMask(Mask, VF, Index) &&\n            │
│ Index == 0)\n      return true;\n    ...\n  }\n\nRationale:\n- Guarding on Limit == VF │
│ prevents passing oversized masks (like length 32) to isExtractSubvectorMask, avoiding  │
│ out-of-bounds mask elements relative to NumOpElts*2.\n- The subsequent code already    │
│ handles cases where Limit % VF == 0 by checking VF-size submasks (identity slices), so │
│ functionality for larger masks remains intact.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe crash stems from │
│ misusing isExtractSubvectorMask with an oversized mask in                              │
│ BaseShuffleAnalysis::isIdentityMask. Adding a size guard (Limit == VF) before calling  │
│ isExtractSubvectorMask enforces the API's preconditions and prevents the assertion.    │
│ This fix preserves existing behavior for proper mask sizes and leverages the existing  │
│ handling of larger masks via the identity-slice logic."})                              │
