│ The fix involves guarding the call to ShuffleVectorInst::isExtractSubvectorMask within │
│ BaseShuffleAnalysis::isIdentityMask to ensure the mask size matches the vector size,   │
│ preventing out-of-bounds assertions in IR utilities.                                   │
│                                                                                        │
│ Patch summary:                                                                         │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                │
│ - Change in isIdentityMask: Only invoke isExtractSubvectorMask when Limit == VF.       │
│                                                                                        │
│ Diff snippet:                                                                          │
│ - Replace:                                                                             │
│   if (!IsStrict) {                                                                     │
│     // Consider extract subvector starting from index 0.                               │
│     if (ShuffleVectorInst::isExtractSubvectorMask(Mask, VF, Index) &&                  │
│         Index == 0)                                                                    │
│       return true;                                                                     │
│     // All VF-size submasks are identity ...                                           │
│ - With:                                                                                │
│   if (!IsStrict) {                                                                     │
│     // Consider extract subvector starting from index 0, only if mask size             │
│     // matches the vector size to satisfy isExtractSubvectorMask preconditions.        │
│     if (Limit == VF &&                                                                 │
│         ShuffleVectorInst::isExtractSubvectorMask(Mask, VF, Index) &&                  │
│         Index == 0)                                                                    │
│       return true;                                                                     │
│     // All VF-size submasks are identity ...                                           │
│                                                                                        │
│ This preserves functionality for valid masks while avoiding misuse of                  │
│ isExtractSubvectorMask that led to the crash.                                          │
│                                                                                        │
│ No other behavioral changes are introduced.                                            │
